Author: Robin Sharma
My Review:
This book is a glorified piece of shit. Author used best seller ingredients to cook this one up but it felt boring and full of cliches.
It seemed author was trying to make a mystical feeling like alchemist by painting India as land of mysticism and enlightenment and throwing some words like yogi, sivana, ancient, etc. every now and then. But the pattern of narration failed the purpose. It felt like I was reading some interviews.
These self help books supposed to leave some impact on readers life but this one failed for me since I wasn’t able to relate to any character or any conversation. Everything seemed out from pure imagination
